  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1Ch 15:1-24. David Brings the Ark from Obededom.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. David made him houses in the city of David—Through the liberality of his Tyrian ally (1Ch 14:1), David was enabled to erect not only a palace for himself, but to furnish suitable accommodation for his numerous family. Where polygamy prevails, each wife has a separate house or suite of apartments for herself and children.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "prepared a place for the ark of God, and pitched for it a tent—that is, made an entirely new one upon the model of the former. The old tabernacle, which Moses had constructed in the wilderness and which had hitherto served the purpose of a sacred covering, was to be left at Gibeon, either because of the unwillingness of the inhabitants to part with such a venerable relic, or because there was no use for it in Jerusalem, where a more solid and sumptuous edifice was contemplated. If it appear surprising that David \"made him houses\" before he prepared this new tabernacle, it should be remembered that he had received no divine intimation respecting such a work.David, having prepared a place for the ark, ordereth the priests and Levites to bring it from Obed-edom,  1 Chronicles 15:1-24. He performeth the solemnity thereof with great joy,  1 Chronicles 15:25-28. Michal despiseth him,  1 Chronicles 15:29.  Houses;  a palace consisting of many houses or apartments for his several wives and children. Pitched for it a tent. Quest. Why did he not first fetch the tabernacle of Moses from Gibeon, where it now was that so he might put the ark into its proper place? Answ. Partly because he had no motion or direction from God concerning the tabernacle, as he had concerning the ark; and partly because he thought the tabernacle was not so necessary for that end as formerly, seeing he intended forthwith to set upon the building of the temple, as appears from  1Ch 12. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "prepared a place for the ark of God, and pitched for it a tent—that is, made an entirely new one upon the model of the former. The old tabernacle, which Moses had constructed in the wilderness and which had hitherto served the purpose of a sacred covering, was to be left at Gibeon, either because of the unwillingness of the inhabitants to part with such a venerable relic, or because there was no use for it in Jerusalem, where a more solid and sumptuous edifice was contemplated. If it appear surprising that David \"made him houses\" before he prepared this new tabernacle, it should be remembered that he had received no divine intimation respecting such a work.David, having prepared a place for the ark, ordereth the priests and Levites to bring it from Obed-edom, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " 1 Chronicles 15:1-24",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". He performeth the solemnity thereof with great joy, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " 1 Chronicles 15:25-28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Michal despiseth him, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " 1 Chronicles 15:29",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "p",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Houses; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " a palace consisting of many houses or apartments for his several wives and children. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Pitched for it a tent.",
            "children": []
          },
